						<summary>

						<p>On a stone beam over the steps of the well called Sūḷebhāvi. The record is in late characters and is dated in Pārthiva, ba. 5.</p>						

						<p>It seems to refer to the setting up of an image of Triyaṁbaka. The inscription is much mutilated.</p>						

						</summary>
